<ul>
<li>use the <code>-p</code> option to publish the port on your host, e.g. publishing the port 8080</li>
<li>use the <code>-e</code> option to specify an environment variable for this container instance</li>
<li>use the <code>-d</code> option to detach the container from the process used to run the container, i.e. start it in the background progress that does not occupy your terminal window</li>
<li>use the <code>--rm</code> option to remove the container once it is stopped</li>
<li>use the <code>--name</code> option to provide a custom name for the container</li>
</ul>
